and thus conquer lands towards the south, in Nubia, 

233
00:14:35,355 --> 00:14:38,355
or towards the north-east, for example in the 15th century BC.

234
00:14:38,355 --> 00:14:42,355
C = The North became distant and ran the risk of gaining independence,

235
00:14:43,284 --> 00:14:47,594
which caused a power vacuum. If this internal depression in Egyptian space  

236
00:14:47,594 --> 00:14:52,240
had come at the same time as an external pressure, there would have been a risk of invasion. 

237
00:14:52,240 --> 00:14:55,960
Faced with the threat, the seat of power was displaced towards the North according 

238
00:14:56,429 --> 00:15:00,429
to the Constantinople principle. D = In turn, the southern part of Egypt became independent. 

239
00:15:00,749 --> 00:15:04,749
If the disunited empire  hadn’t resisted, Egypt would have been conquered. 

240
00:15:05,235 --> 00:15:09,065
In the North, a decentered capital represented the invading power, with the conquest 

241
